<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?mso-infoPathSolution PIVersion="1.0.0.0" href="file:///C:\ProgramData\Carisbrooke%20Shipping%20Ltd\ISM%20Dashboard\Repository\Forms\Technical%20and%20Safety\RAF%20-%20Risk%20Assessment%20Form%20v2.xsn" name="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:infopath:RAF---Risk-Assessment-Form:-myXSD-2010-09-08T18-23-10" solutionVersion="6.0.0.0" productVersion="14.0.0" ?><?mso-application progid="InfoPath.Document" versionProgid="InfoPath.Document.2"?><my:Main my:DateCreated="" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:od="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:officedata" xmlns:my="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/infopath/2003/myXSD/2010-09-08T18:23:10" xmlns:xd="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/infopath/2003" xml:lang="en-gb"><my:Details><my:Number>D 03</my:Number><my:Title>Tug Operation (incl. Towing, Mooring, Unmooring)</my:Title></my:Details><my:Hazards><my:Hazard my:HazardId="1"><my:Description>Personal injuries</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided. Use portable lighting if required; 
c) Emergency stops tested and ready; 
d) Crew vigilance – Constant monitoring of the task; 
e) Sufficient number of crew to be made available; 
f) Any crew not directly involved in towing operations should stay well clear; 
g) Master to monitor the progress of the operation and crew and to give clear and concise orders; 
h) Winch / windlass must not be left unattended whilst in use; 
i) Ropes must not be used to operate the winch/windlass controls; 
j) Crew should keep clear of all moving parts; 
k) Ensure the towing line is slack when the crew make it fast to the bollard(s); 
l) Crew should stay clear of the towing line(s) and bollard(s) were towing line is made fast.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>2</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="2"><my:Description>Towing line(s) parting</my:Description><my:Severity>3</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>2</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) All crew involved to be briefed; 
b) Vessel's lines, if being used, to be visually inspected prior to use and replaced if required; 
c) Crew vigilance - Constant monitoring of the task; 
d) All crew to stay clear of snap-back zones; 
e) Crew should stay clear of the towing line(s) and bollard(s) were towing line is made fast.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="3"><my:Description>Lack of and / or improper communication between the bridge and mooring station</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) All crew involved to be briefed; 
b) VHF radio check prior to operations; 
c) Use of the English language in clear and concise orders; 
d) Use of headphones in conjunction with the VHF; 
e) Stop any unnecessary ventilation in the vicinity of the mooring stations to reduce noise.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="4"><my:Description>Lack of and / or improper communication between the vessel’s crew and tug boat</my:Description><my:Severity>3</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>OOW should show clear instructions to the tug boat Master from a visible position on deck.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="5"><my:Description>Slips, trips and falls</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Trip hazards to be clearly marked; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided. Use portable lighting if required; 
c) Anti-slip surface at mooring station to be properly maintained.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="6"><my:Description>Towing line caught in propeller</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Gearbox / CPP in neutral; 
b) Minimum slack on mooring rope; 
c) Smooth and efficient rope handling.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>2</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="7"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="8"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="9"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="10"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard></my:Hazards><my:Review><my:ReviewerName></my:ReviewerName><my:ReviewerRank></my:ReviewerRank><my:ReviewDate>2015-12-09</my:ReviewDate><my:ReviewLocation></my:ReviewLocation><my:ReviewMembers></my:ReviewMembers></my:Review